WEBVTT

00:00.375 --> 00:02.417
[Deena] Previously
on What About Brian:

00:02.417 --> 00:04.417
You could sell these
and make a fortune.

00:04.417 --> 00:05.917
Do you think I could do it?

00:05.917 --> 00:08.417
Hi, I have a delivery
for Natasha Drew.

00:08.417 --> 00:11.375
I wasn't expecting a package.

00:11.375 --> 00:15.083
I'm sorry to hear
about your divorce. Not
that I couldn't see it coming.

00:16.041 --> 00:17.875
- [grunting]
- [bell rings]

00:20.417 --> 00:23.834
[Stephanie] My movie premieres
this week. Will you
be my "plus one"?

00:29.625 --> 00:31.583
Laura. I got them.

00:31.583 --> 00:34.250
Let me see. Cheesy magazines,
they make me so happy.

00:34.250 --> 00:35.917
I know. Me too.

00:35.917 --> 00:37.417
Especially when I'm in them.

00:37.417 --> 00:40.000
OK, I'll take these,
you take these.

00:43.417 --> 00:44.750
Oh, my God!

00:47.583 --> 00:51.125
This one has a poll
with me and someone else
in the same dress and I won.

00:51.125 --> 00:55.291
Seventy-six percent
of the people say that
I look better than Lisa Rinna.

00:56.125 --> 00:57.667
Did you guys steal my paper?

00:57.667 --> 00:59.875
And then rob a newsstand?

00:59.875 --> 01:00.959
What's going on here?

01:00.959 --> 01:02.959
We're looking
for Stephanie pictures.

01:02.959 --> 01:04.166
How's my butt?

01:04.166 --> 01:06.250
Can I have
my sports section now?

01:06.250 --> 01:08.458
And a hello would be nice.

01:08.458 --> 01:09.959
- Hi, there.
- Hey.

01:14.208 --> 01:16.125
- Thank you.
- [gasps]

01:18.417 --> 01:19.458
What?

01:19.458 --> 01:21.500
Is that a picture of me
in skinny jeans?

01:21.500 --> 01:23.125
I knew they were
on the way out.

01:26.458 --> 01:29.166
- It can't be that bad.
- It's nothing.

01:29.166 --> 01:30.625
It's a picture
of us. Forget it.

01:30.625 --> 01:32.709
- Oh, come on.
- [laughing]

01:32.709 --> 01:34.542
Give it to me. All right.

01:42.125 --> 01:44.959
What does this even mean?
"Worst accessory"?

01:44.959 --> 01:47.208
It's nothing.
Just forget about it.

01:47.208 --> 01:50.083
It's one of those things they do
with red carpet pictures.

01:50.083 --> 01:52.583
When someone has an ugly purse
or bad jewelry.

01:52.583 --> 01:54.709
No, they mean me.
I'm the worst accessory.

01:54.709 --> 01:57.709
No. Maybe they just
mean the white socks
with the black suit.

01:57.709 --> 01:58.750
No, they mean him.

02:00.208 --> 02:01.834
What? It's no big deal.

02:01.834 --> 02:03.834
Look, Ben Affleck
has worst sunglasses.

02:03.834 --> 02:07.834
I have those sunglasses.
And second of all, I am those
sunglasses now.

02:07.834 --> 02:11.208
Do you have any idea
what kind of crap
I'm going to get for this?

02:11.208 --> 02:15.417
For the rest of my life?
We have to contain this.
Do not tell a soul. No one.

02:15.417 --> 02:18.625
- But that's...
- No one.

02:19.458 --> 02:21.375
[pop music plays]

02:23.041 --> 02:25.792
What is this junk?

02:28.625 --> 02:31.125
Yeah, hi. I'd like
to cancel a subscription.

02:31.125 --> 02:34.458
It's under Heather Hillman.
Mm-hm.

02:38.208 --> 02:39.667
Wait, I'll call you back.

02:44.041 --> 02:48.792
- Dave, where are you?
- Getting a coffee and a muffin.

02:48.792 --> 02:51.500
Hey, do you guys get
Celebrity Beat magazine?

02:51.500 --> 02:53.750
No. Why, do you?
And if so, why?

02:53.750 --> 02:57.083
Look, it was Heather's, OK?
What... Hang on a second.

02:57.083 --> 02:59.750
[phone ringing]

02:59.750 --> 03:04.834
Hey, uh, look, just get it, OK?
Page 12. You'll thank me later.

03:04.834 --> 03:06.750
All right. Fine.

03:06.750 --> 03:09.125
[dialing]

03:09.125 --> 03:10.917
- Hey.
- [Deena] Hi.

03:10.917 --> 03:13.917
- Hey, we get Celebrity Beat
magazine?
- Why?

03:13.917 --> 03:16.583
- I don't know.
Adam told me to get it.
- We don't get it.

03:16.583 --> 03:18.333
Hold on a second. Jackpot.

03:19.375 --> 03:20.750
Page 12. Page...

03:20.750 --> 03:23.709
Mommy, I wanted to wear
the red sweater today.

03:23.709 --> 03:26.542
You can wear it tomorrow,
sweetie. Dave, I got to go.

03:26.542 --> 03:28.417
This is fantastic, Deen.

03:28.417 --> 03:30.959
Buy me one. I'm dropping
the girls off at school.

03:30.959 --> 03:32.083
OK. Whose school?

03:32.083 --> 03:35.250
Their school.
What is the matter with you?

03:35.250 --> 03:36.750
Me? Nothing's
wrong with me.

03:36.750 --> 03:39.917
I just think you should get in
and get out as fast as possible.

03:39.917 --> 03:42.291
OK.

03:42.291 --> 03:47.333
Oh, hey. Sharon. Is Tracey still
on for our play date
at our house today?

03:47.333 --> 03:49.959
Maybe Geneva should
come to our house instead.

03:49.959 --> 03:53.166
- Really?
- Or maybe we
should just re-schedule.

03:53.166 --> 03:58.083
Hi. There is Larissa's
permission slip
for the field trip.

03:58.083 --> 04:00.250
- Thanks for volunteering.
- No problem.

04:00.250 --> 04:01.709
I'm looking forward to it.

04:01.709 --> 04:06.750
I think I was Geneva's chaperone
to the La Brea Tar Pits as well.

04:10.625 --> 04:14.667
OK, uh, is something going on?
Something wrong?

04:14.667 --> 04:17.333
Did Larissa bite someone again?
We talked to her...

04:17.333 --> 04:20.834
Mrs. Greco, it's not your
daughter, it's your husband.

04:20.834 --> 04:23.583
Dave? What did he do?

04:23.583 --> 04:26.542
Your husband attacked Richard
Rovich on school property

04:26.542 --> 04:28.041
in front of all the kids.

04:28.041 --> 04:31.792
They were wrestling
on the ground like
two little... kids.

04:36.875 --> 04:39.542
- Yeah?
- Hello.

04:39.542 --> 04:43.959
Ronnie said I could come in.
I have the, uh... the documents.

04:46.834 --> 04:48.000
Hi.

04:51.792 --> 04:54.542
- I got to lock the door.
- There's no lock on the door.

04:54.542 --> 04:56.542
- Oh, really?
- Ronnie keeps them out.

04:56.542 --> 04:59.000
She's a pit bull.

04:59.000 --> 05:03.667
Now let's rotate the babies'
legs like a bicycle.

05:03.667 --> 05:06.875
Sorry, I'm late. I...

05:06.875 --> 05:10.709
Bella always gets cranky
when I... when I have
to wake her up from her nap.

05:10.709 --> 05:14.875
- You should never
wake a sleeping baby.
- Yes, we'll get to that.

05:14.875 --> 05:18.375
Right now, Nicole,
Cynthia was telling us
about Dylan's diaper rash.

05:18.375 --> 05:23.000
It's not going away and I call
the pediatrician every day

05:23.000 --> 05:25.542
and she just says to put
more diaper rash cream on.

05:25.542 --> 05:27.542
I'm thinking of just switching.

05:27.542 --> 05:30.208
- Creams?
- No, doctors.

05:30.208 --> 05:34.917
I'm sure it will be OK.
It's just a diaper rash, right?
Don't all babies get it?

05:34.917 --> 05:37.750
Everyone has their
own problems, Nicole.

05:37.750 --> 05:40.458
And we like to keep
this class a judge-free zone.

05:40.458 --> 05:43.291
- I wasn't...
- Maybe you'd like
to share something?

05:43.291 --> 05:47.250
Well, actually,
there is something that
I'd like some advice on. Yeah.

05:47.250 --> 05:50.417
And since we're
all strangers here,
maybe this is a safe place.

05:50.417 --> 05:51.917
OK.

05:51.917 --> 05:53.792
I slept with
my brother's friend Adam.

05:53.792 --> 05:56.417
And keeping this
secret is killing me.

05:56.417 --> 05:58.625
You haven't told him
he's the father?

05:58.625 --> 06:01.291
He's not the father.
This happened the other night.

06:01.291 --> 06:05.166
The point is that it's
just keeping a secret from
everyone... our friends.

06:05.166 --> 06:08.250
And, you know, Brian...
That's my brother...

06:08.250 --> 06:12.208
I don't know what he
would do if he found out
and I'm feeling so guilty.

06:12.208 --> 06:16.625
And I'm just wondering does
anyone think that I should tell?

06:18.834 --> 06:23.250
I'm not sure that's
quite what mommy
and baby classes are about.

06:23.250 --> 06:27.792
OK, let's pick up our babies
and move to circle time.

06:39.291 --> 06:42.125
- [rock music plays]
- [panting]

06:46.625 --> 06:48.667
Morning.

06:48.667 --> 06:51.417
♪ Well, I've been
driving wrong ♪

06:51.417 --> 06:54.917
♪ Way up your
one-way street ♪

06:54.917 --> 06:58.542
Don't do that. What, did
you learn that from Natasha?

06:58.542 --> 07:03.667
- Morning. What's up?
- These. Sketches. Life Sucks.

07:03.667 --> 07:08.000
OK. Our hero gets depressed,
falls down a little
sewer grid here.

07:08.000 --> 07:11.333
He's got to battle
all his exes until
he gets back up to the top.

07:11.333 --> 07:13.250
- These are good.
- Yeah?

07:13.250 --> 07:16.000
- You can show
them to boss-zilla soon?
- Definitely.

07:16.000 --> 07:20.291
Good.
Anything else?

07:20.291 --> 07:25.458
No. It's 10:00am, buddy.
What else do you want?
I mean it's not the Army.

07:25.458 --> 07:26.959
Right.

07:29.000 --> 07:34.083
♪ Hard way up
and a long way down ♪

07:34.875 --> 07:37.625
Very funny. You guys.

07:37.625 --> 07:39.959
If only you could be
this creative all the time.

07:50.208 --> 07:54.250
- You do this all by yourself?
- No. Natasha helped.

07:54.250 --> 07:58.417
- She came up
with the screen saver.
- That's just... wrong.

07:59.834 --> 08:02.375
And funny.
Don't forget funny.

08:06.250 --> 08:08.834
Natasha, I know you're in there.

08:14.500 --> 08:18.000
- What are you doing here?
- I can't tell you that.

08:18.000 --> 08:22.583
See, there's a thing called
lawyer/client confidentiality.

08:22.583 --> 08:24.917
Can we, uh,
help you with something?

08:24.917 --> 08:27.792
No. Nothing.

08:27.792 --> 08:30.917
Forget it.
I'll talk to you later.

08:30.917 --> 08:34.208
Oh, hey. And,
don't worry. I saw it.

08:34.208 --> 08:36.709
Those white socks
are really hard to miss.

08:44.875 --> 08:49.417
- God, that was close.
- Yeah. Ronnie is so fired.

08:49.417 --> 08:51.625
Yeah. Jeez.

08:51.625 --> 08:53.750
[♪ Low Stars:
Calling All Friends]

08:53.750 --> 08:58.250
♪ Calling all friends and
people I met on the way down ♪

08:58.250 --> 09:03.625
♪ Calling all friends
and people I don't even know ♪

09:03.625 --> 09:05.750
♪ Calling on high ♪

09:05.750 --> 09:10.625
♪ I want to believe
there's a way now ♪

09:10.625 --> 09:15.625
♪ I'm too tired to pretend
I don't wanna be alone ♪

09:15.625 --> 09:18.458
♪ I'm calling all friends ♪♪

09:25.000 --> 09:27.750
Hey, honey.
So, how was class?

09:27.750 --> 09:29.583
They all hate me.

09:29.583 --> 09:33.000
Give it time.
The moms can be a little
bit judgmental at first.

09:33.000 --> 09:36.959
Who cares? It doesn't matter.
It's not about me,
it's about us.

09:36.959 --> 09:39.792
I thought we were having lunch.
This place looks closed.

09:39.792 --> 09:43.500
The article in LA Magazine?
The one that's coming
out in a few days?

09:43.500 --> 09:46.166
- Hottest cupcake in LA?
- Uh-huh.

09:46.166 --> 09:49.291
Last year when my band was
featured they became a success.

09:49.291 --> 09:52.583
- So?
- So welcome
to "Icing on the Cupcake."

09:58.834 --> 10:01.333
Please don't be saying
what I think you're saying.

10:01.333 --> 10:04.542
I am. We just
assumed this lease.
We can afford it.

10:04.542 --> 10:07.458
I ran the numbers. The rent's
cheap, the location's great.

10:07.458 --> 10:10.083
It used to be a bakery.
We can open right away.

10:10.083 --> 10:13.500
- I don't know.
- What's there to know?
It's a done deal.

10:13.500 --> 10:17.875
We're really going
to have our own business.
Just like Dave and Brian.

10:17.875 --> 10:22.125
Well, when do we have
to have this place ready?
You know, realistically?

10:22.125 --> 10:23.125
Yesterday.

10:27.875 --> 10:31.083
[Adam] Maybe we shouldn't
do this at your office anymore.

10:31.083 --> 10:33.250
We don't want people
getting suspicious.

10:33.250 --> 10:36.208
Yeah, sure. That's fine.

10:36.208 --> 10:40.333
Here's the thing,
I think you're a great girl.

10:40.333 --> 10:43.041
Wait. You're kidding me,
right?

10:43.041 --> 10:47.000
Well, it's just that,
I'm not really looking
for a relationship right now.

10:47.000 --> 10:50.834
Relationship? Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.
Who said anything
about a relationship?

10:50.834 --> 10:52.792
I just assumed
that that's where...

10:52.792 --> 10:56.375
OK. All right. Maybe we need
to set some ground rules.

10:56.375 --> 10:58.959
We don't need to talk
about how our day was

10:58.959 --> 11:01.709
or how work was.
I don't care.

11:01.709 --> 11:03.875
Sweet. Neither do I.

11:03.875 --> 11:07.834
Good. And I don't need
to know where you grew up
or what your mother's name is

11:07.834 --> 11:10.417
or when your birthday is.
Nothing.

11:10.417 --> 11:13.583
We don't need to discuss
how you're feeling
or how I'm feeling

11:13.583 --> 11:17.250
or what we're thinking.
We're not going to ask.

11:17.250 --> 11:19.959
- That is so fantastic.
- Good.

11:19.959 --> 11:22.250
- Yeah.
- I'm going to get back to work.

11:22.250 --> 11:25.875
- Hey, I don't care.
- Right.

11:37.333 --> 11:40.500
Were you ever going to tell me
you punched Richard?

11:40.500 --> 11:43.083
- I didn't punch Richard.
- You didn't?

11:43.083 --> 11:45.375
- No.
- Uh-huh.

11:45.375 --> 11:48.083
- We sort of wrestled.
- Dave.

11:48.083 --> 11:52.792
Deena. Look, come on.
Deen, he started it.

11:52.792 --> 11:56.625
He started it? Wow.
What are you, five?

11:56.625 --> 12:01.959
OK. Fine. Fine. I did it.
I did it and I'm sorry, OK?

12:01.959 --> 12:04.792
- You're not mad at me, are you?
- I'm not mad at you.

12:04.792 --> 12:07.875
But, I mean, come on,
it's just a little embarrassing

12:07.875 --> 12:11.250
that I have to
send you to chaperone
Larissa's field trip.

12:11.250 --> 12:15.250
- Hold on a sec.
You're chaperoning.
- No.

12:15.250 --> 12:17.792
Yes, because I have
a little thing called work

12:17.792 --> 12:20.792
- that I go to every day, Deena.
- Hm.

12:20.792 --> 12:22.375
What's that? What's the look?

12:22.375 --> 12:27.625
Yeah, in case you forgot,
I have to open
a cupcake store that day.

12:27.625 --> 12:30.792
- Thank you, Maria.
- You're welcome.
The girls have eaten.

12:30.792 --> 12:32.250
- Great.
- Good night, Maria.

12:32.250 --> 12:34.959
What cupcake store?
What are you talking about?

12:34.959 --> 12:38.500
How can I forget about something
I don't even know about?

12:38.500 --> 12:41.667
I own a cupcake store now.
Yeah, me and Nicole.

12:41.667 --> 12:46.792
Just a six month lease.
We just thought we'd
give it a shot.

12:46.792 --> 12:48.208
What?

12:48.208 --> 12:52.000
- Oh.
- What "Oh, what"? What is it?

12:53.375 --> 12:55.291
It's a notice from the court.

12:58.792 --> 13:03.500
We have to file our divorce
paperwork next week or start
the process all over.

13:03.500 --> 13:06.458
- Divorce paperwork. That's fun.
- Yes.

13:06.458 --> 13:09.750
So, what are we going to do?
Nothing, right?

13:10.375 --> 13:11.834
Yes. Nothing.

13:11.834 --> 13:16.458
Just... keep doing
what we're doing.

13:16.458 --> 13:19.375
Right. What is it
that we're doing again?

13:19.375 --> 13:21.166
- Dating.
- Yeah.

13:21.166 --> 13:23.750
Secretly. We're moving forward.

13:23.750 --> 13:26.834
And as long as we're moving
forward then that's good, right?

13:26.834 --> 13:30.625
- Yeah, right. It's great.
- Yeah, it's great. It's good.

13:32.583 --> 13:35.250
So, can we talk about
this cupcake store for a second?

13:35.250 --> 13:39.083
[electronic music plays]

13:42.125 --> 13:46.041
I hate to say this,
but we're going to be late
if we don't go.

13:46.041 --> 13:49.792
Wouldn't you rather
just stay here than go
to that stupid restaurant?

13:49.792 --> 13:53.375
I thought you were the one
that wanted to go.

13:53.375 --> 13:57.917
- Well, this could work.
- [phone ringing]

13:59.667 --> 14:03.792
- It's my manager.
I have to get this.
- Yeah.

14:05.709 --> 14:06.750
Hello.

14:06.750 --> 14:08.125
What do you want
on your pizza?

14:08.125 --> 14:10.208
Actually, we're
going out to eat.

14:11.583 --> 14:14.083
- What's that face?
- Just my regular face.

14:14.083 --> 14:19.333
- I'll let Stephanie tell you.
- Tell me what? You ready?

14:19.333 --> 14:22.625
- I thought we were staying in?
- We have a reservation.

14:22.625 --> 14:25.458
This has nothing to do
with the way I feel about you.

14:25.458 --> 14:28.375
So don't take it personally
because I really like you.

14:28.375 --> 14:31.500
Are you breaking up with me?
Because we're not even a couple.

14:31.500 --> 14:34.750
- We haven't even had sex yet.
- Whoa. Too much information.

14:34.750 --> 14:40.583
It's my manager.
She's kind of suggesting
that I re-accessorize.

14:42.041 --> 14:43.583
Sorry, ignore me.

14:43.583 --> 14:45.959
You're taking dating advice
from your manager?

14:45.959 --> 14:48.583
No, not at all.
It's career advice,

14:48.583 --> 14:51.417
and I can't be seen with you
in public for a little while.

14:51.417 --> 14:53.834
Yeah. Why would
I take that personally?

14:53.834 --> 14:56.291
It's not going to be forever.

14:59.000 --> 15:00.083
Sausage OK?

15:05.792 --> 15:09.333
- You're going
to kill your eyes.
- Fluorescent lights depress me.

15:09.333 --> 15:13.917
So buy some better lamps.
We'll even pay for them. Perks.

15:13.917 --> 15:15.667
Speaking of which...

15:15.667 --> 15:19.792
One of our clients owns the
Atheneum Hotel in Beverly Hills.

15:19.792 --> 15:22.208
Figured you could
use a little fun.

15:22.208 --> 15:24.959
Free dinner, suite,
five-star hotel.

15:24.959 --> 15:28.125
You think you can scare
someone up to go with you?

15:28.125 --> 15:29.166
I think I can.

15:29.166 --> 15:33.500
Good. Have fun, relax.
One other thing.

15:33.500 --> 15:36.625
A Guy Rowland is going
to be in town for a few days.

15:36.625 --> 15:38.959
He works for Coopertan
Manufacturing.

15:38.959 --> 15:40.500
So you need me
to talk to him?

15:40.500 --> 15:43.333
He knows a lot about the car
locks that Coopertan makes.

15:43.333 --> 15:45.959
- Like what?
- Like whether
they're faulty or not.

15:45.959 --> 15:49.583
We need him to sign this
statement saying
that they're not.

15:52.959 --> 15:56.000
It's already written. Do I need
a witness to authenticate it?

15:56.000 --> 16:00.583
- There's no need for that.
- We already wrote this for him
without his knowledge.

16:00.583 --> 16:02.417
What if he doesn't
agree to sign it?

16:02.417 --> 16:06.041
That's what you're there for,
Hillman. Don't leave
without a signature.

16:06.041 --> 16:10.041
You're authorized
to do whatever it takes.
I have faith in you.

16:10.041 --> 16:11.458
Enjoy the hotel.

16:19.959 --> 16:22.250
[woman] This is
my very own recipe.

16:22.250 --> 16:25.917
I call it Cynthia's
Carrot Concoction.

16:25.917 --> 16:29.625
I'm so sorry. I could've sworn
that I made enough for everyone.

16:31.375 --> 16:33.375
You make your own baby food?

16:33.375 --> 16:37.542
Do you know how many
preservatives are
in processed baby food?

16:37.542 --> 16:40.333
I'm sorry about
what I said the other day.

16:40.333 --> 16:44.125
I was nervous
and I wanted to fit in.

16:44.125 --> 16:46.750
Well, that's OK.
It must be hard
for you at your age.

16:48.917 --> 16:53.000
OK, ladies, time to gather
your babies. Playtime is over.

16:57.917 --> 16:59.709
Wait.

16:59.709 --> 17:01.875
- How much would
you pay for a cupcake?
- What?

17:01.875 --> 17:05.083
My friend and I are opening
