Maybe I punched Richard
because I want to show people.

33:26.583 --> 33:31.875
I want to tell them that you're
mine. I want you to tell them.

33:31.875 --> 33:34.417
Why do you have
one foot out the door?

33:34.417 --> 33:38.208
I am not keeping
one foot out the door, Dave.

33:38.208 --> 33:42.083
I'm trying to protect
our children from another
huge disappointment.

33:42.083 --> 33:45.917
I'm not going to tell them
or anyone anything

33:45.917 --> 33:48.917
until you can show me
that you can forgive and forget.

33:48.917 --> 33:51.750
And what do you do? You go
out and you punch Richard,

33:51.750 --> 33:54.250
not once, but twice.

33:54.250 --> 33:56.125
I don't even
think about Suzanne.

33:56.125 --> 33:59.458
I don't think about the fact
that you slept with her.

33:59.458 --> 34:02.792
It's gone from my mind!
All I think about is...

34:02.792 --> 34:05.291
...is us and our future.

34:06.291 --> 34:09.125
And until you can do the same,

34:09.125 --> 34:12.875
then you have one
more day until those
divorce papers expire.

34:16.500 --> 34:17.500
It's on you.

34:23.834 --> 34:25.792
I really want a veggie dog,

34:25.792 --> 34:28.500
but that's probably
not the way to go here.

34:28.500 --> 34:30.500
I wonder if they have nachos.

34:32.625 --> 34:35.834
I take it you don't
want to talk about tonight.

34:35.834 --> 34:38.792
Well, whatever.
There's nothing to talk about.

34:38.792 --> 34:40.875
Listen, Brian,

34:40.875 --> 34:44.125
I love Stephanie and I
know her better than anyone.

34:44.125 --> 34:47.291
She's a sweet person.
But this thing that's
happening to her?

34:47.291 --> 34:50.000
It's huge and it's what
she's wanted her entire life.

34:50.000 --> 34:53.625
- What's your point?
- It's not going to change.
It's going to get worse.

34:53.625 --> 34:57.333
There'll be more pictures
and more people who
think you're a waiter,

34:57.333 --> 34:59.500
and really,
really awful parties.

34:59.500 --> 35:02.667
That party was awful.
I don't know how
she convinced you to come.

35:02.667 --> 35:04.667
Honestly?

35:05.667 --> 35:07.333
I wanted to be with you.

35:09.333 --> 35:13.333
And slug the photographers
with my purse if they tried
to take your picture.

35:15.166 --> 35:17.834
You're always looking
after everyone, Brian,

35:17.834 --> 35:21.500
and you need someone
to look after you.

35:25.041 --> 35:28.208
I knew you looked familiar.
You were in Celebrity Beat,
right?

35:28.208 --> 35:31.834
- With Stephanie Conner?
- Yeah. Yeah, that's me.

35:31.834 --> 35:34.208
- You want my autograph?
- Um...

35:34.208 --> 35:35.542
I'm just kidding.

35:37.583 --> 35:40.041
- All right. What do you want?
- Let's see...

35:40.041 --> 35:42.041
- You want a slaw dog.
- I do.

35:46.792 --> 35:50.583
This is unexpected.
I don't do unexpected.

35:50.583 --> 35:53.542
You look good in your
"hanging around the house"
clothes.

35:53.542 --> 35:55.667
Stop that.

35:55.667 --> 35:59.667
What? I've only seen
you dressed up or undressed.
Nothing in between.

35:59.667 --> 36:03.500
OK, you're flirting with me,
all right? Another rule.

36:03.500 --> 36:07.208
- No flirting unless in bed.
- Can we stop with the rules,
please?

36:07.208 --> 36:09.417
Look, I need
to talk to you, OK?

36:09.417 --> 36:12.250
I need to talk to someone
who will understand.

36:12.250 --> 36:14.583
What makes you think
I'm going to understand?

36:14.583 --> 36:17.750
I'm sure you've done something
to get ahead in your career.

36:17.750 --> 36:19.709
Something that you knew
wasn't right

36:19.709 --> 36:23.333
but you did it anyway.
Am I right?

36:26.458 --> 36:29.458
OK. All right,
we can talk tonight.

36:29.458 --> 36:31.709
But that means no sex.

36:31.709 --> 36:34.250
You can have one or the other
but not both.

36:34.250 --> 36:36.709
OK, I need to talk.

36:36.709 --> 36:41.500
But if you tell anyone
that I picked talking over sex,
I'll deny it.

36:43.333 --> 36:44.834
- Come in.
- All right.

36:54.291 --> 36:58.291
[Stephanie clears throat]

37:00.125 --> 37:01.834
What are you doing?

37:01.834 --> 37:06.542
I'm giving you the signal.
Unless you're embarrassed by me.

37:13.041 --> 37:15.917
Look, I'm sorry
about tonight.

37:15.917 --> 37:19.041
I'm still getting
used to all of this.

37:19.041 --> 37:20.959
Is the party over?

37:20.959 --> 37:23.959
No, it was just
getting started.

37:23.959 --> 37:25.834
And you still left?

37:25.834 --> 37:30.875
Yeah, I was looking around,
holding my free phone,

37:30.875 --> 37:34.041
and I saw all these other people
holding free phones and...

37:34.041 --> 37:37.834
I know, and it seemed
so empty and meaningless.

37:37.834 --> 37:40.667
No, it was
actually pretty fun.

37:40.667 --> 37:44.291
I just wished that you
were there with me.

37:45.875 --> 37:48.625
You know? To enjoy it.

37:48.625 --> 37:51.000
And to get your
own free phone.

37:53.959 --> 37:58.667
All I know is that I definitely
don't want to screw us up.

37:58.667 --> 38:02.083
Wait, hold on.
We're an "us"?

38:04.667 --> 38:08.333
Seriously, though,
no more hiding.

38:08.333 --> 38:10.500
How about tomorrow
we go out

38:10.500 --> 38:13.625
and I'll be your accessory.

38:17.709 --> 38:22.542
Or we can just
stay in all day.

38:22.542 --> 38:25.083
[rock music plays]

38:25.083 --> 38:28.083
♪ It makes me feel
like everything's
gonna be all right ♪

38:28.083 --> 38:32.166
♪ It makes me feel
like everything's
gonna be all right ♪

38:34.208 --> 38:37.375
I don't know, honey. Do you
really think that'll work?

38:37.375 --> 38:40.166
Of course it will. I'm
going to call Brian right now.

38:40.166 --> 38:42.959
I'll meet you
in the store in an hour.

38:42.959 --> 38:43.959
OK.

38:45.208 --> 38:47.709
Girls, who wants
cupcakes for breakfast?

38:47.709 --> 38:49.083
- I do.
- I do.

38:49.083 --> 38:51.208
- Yeah.
- I want vanilla.

38:51.208 --> 38:53.000
[phone vibrating]

39:02.917 --> 39:05.458
Hey, Nic. You OK?

39:05.458 --> 39:09.458
Wait, you're talking
so fast I can barely
make out what you're saying.

39:12.291 --> 39:15.041
Yeah. Yeah, I'll ask.

39:15.041 --> 39:18.208
All right, calm down.
I'll see you later.

39:18.208 --> 39:22.750
Hey, remember when you
said you were willing
to be my accessory for today?

39:22.750 --> 39:24.083
Yeah?

39:25.291 --> 39:27.750
How do you feel
about cupcakes?

39:30.083 --> 39:33.417
These are the best
cupcakes in town.
I try to eat one every day.

39:33.417 --> 39:36.875
Any flavor.
Especially the red velvet.

39:37.834 --> 39:40.166
I hope this is working.

39:40.166 --> 39:43.625
It already is. I know
how to get a crowd,
she knows how to work one.

39:43.625 --> 39:45.875
True.

39:45.875 --> 39:50.417
Mommy, look what I made.
Isn't this just
the best cupcakes?

39:50.417 --> 39:52.333
Sweeties,
those are beautiful.

39:52.333 --> 39:55.917
Can you please go
make me some more? OK.

40:01.500 --> 40:04.125
This place looks so amazing.
Congratulations.

40:04.125 --> 40:05.959
- Thanks.
- Now give me a cupcake.

40:05.959 --> 40:08.792
Well, of course.

40:08.792 --> 40:12.417
Hey, thank you
so much for bringing Stephanie.
She's just awesome.

40:12.417 --> 40:16.709
Yeah. Yeah.
She's actually pretty great.

40:21.667 --> 40:25.500
I'm going to go give
Stephanie advice
on how to handle the media.

40:25.500 --> 40:28.667
Don't do that. Trust me.

40:28.667 --> 40:31.709
- You know Stephanie Conner?
- She goes out with my brother.

40:31.709 --> 40:35.709
You know what? You were right
and we were being judgmental.

40:35.709 --> 40:38.375
Look at this place.
It's doing so well,

40:38.375 --> 40:41.000
and we just would really
like to be a part of it.

40:41.000 --> 40:43.333
Just to support
one of our own, you know?

40:43.333 --> 40:44.959
Great, thanks.

40:44.959 --> 40:48.333
Hey, so Nic, what ever happened
to that guy Adam you slept with?

40:48.333 --> 40:52.000
It was your brother's
best friend, right?

40:52.000 --> 40:55.208
So tell me, did you ever tell?

40:55.208 --> 40:57.959
Tell me she's talking
about a different brother.

40:57.959 --> 41:00.792
- I'm going to take this.
- It didn't ring.

41:01.875 --> 41:03.875
I got to make some cupcakes.

41:03.875 --> 41:06.291
Ha! It wasn't me!

41:06.291 --> 41:08.500
Cupcakes for everyone on me!

41:11.250 --> 41:13.291
- Stephanie Conner's in there.
- Yeah?

41:13.291 --> 41:16.125
This place is going
to be huge now.

41:16.125 --> 41:17.709
Yeah. I know.

41:19.667 --> 41:23.208
Babe, you would not believe the
day I had at the store today.

41:23.208 --> 41:25.875
Stephanie came in and...

41:25.875 --> 41:28.542
[soft rock plays]

41:28.542 --> 41:29.959
Oh, Dave.

41:33.166 --> 41:35.834
- Hi.
- Hi.

41:35.834 --> 41:37.250
What are you doing?

41:37.250 --> 41:40.083
Moving forward.
I'm over it, you know?

41:40.083 --> 41:44.750
I'm just... I'm done
living in this storage
closet. I'm sorry.

41:47.041 --> 41:52.709
Really? Because I thought
that maybe we could...

41:52.709 --> 41:54.917
No, no. Listen, listen.

41:54.917 --> 41:59.583
I'm moving out of the
storage closet so I
can be upstairs with you.

41:59.583 --> 42:03.208
♪ Won't you ♪

42:03.208 --> 42:06.834
♪ Be the new one to shine ♪

42:09.375 --> 42:12.417
Will you...
will you marry me,

42:12.417 --> 42:15.875
Deena Greco? Again?

42:15.875 --> 42:19.917
♪ All you have to do
is cry ♪

42:19.917 --> 42:22.375
♪ All you have to do
is cry ♪♪
